sters of Florence]]''\n| [[Cosimo de' Medici]]\n| 8 episodes; also executive producer\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"Medici\"/>\n|-\n| 2017\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Oasis (2017 film)|''Oasis'']]\n| Peter Leigh\n| Pilot\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"Medici\"/>\n|-\n| 2017\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Philip K. Dick's Electric Dreams]]''\n| Agent Ross\n| Anthology series<br>Episode: \"The Hood Maker\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/05/philip-k-dicks-electric-dreams-richard-madden-holiday-grainger-anneika-rose-amazon-anthology-series-1202096582/|title='Philip K. Dick's Electric Dreams': Richard Madden, Holiday Grainger & Anneika Rose Join Amazon's Anthology Series|last=Pedersen|first=Erik|date=18 May 2017|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|access-date=7 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190819001327/https://deadline.com/2017/05/philip-k-dicks-electric-dreams-richard-madden-holiday-grainger-anneika-rose-amazon-anthology-series-1202096582/|archive-date=19 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2018\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Bodyguard (British TV series)|Bodyguard]]''\n| PS David Budd\n| 6 episodes<br/>[[Golden Globe Award for Best Actor \u2013 Television Series Drama]] <small>(2019)</small><br/>[[National Television Awards|National Television Award for Drama Performance]] <small>(2019)</small><br/>Nominated \u2013 [[Critics' Choice Television Award for Best Actor in a Drama Series]] <small>(2019)</small>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"GG\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nationaltvawards.com/winners|title=Winners \u2013 National Television Awards|work=[[National Film Awards]]|access-date=9 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170121153006/http://www.nationaltvawards.com/winners|archive-date=21 January 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/awards/2018/12/10/the-favourite-critics-choice-award-nominations/|title=The Favourite gets huge Oscar boost with 14 Critics Choice Award nominations|last=Nolfi|first=Joey|date=10 December 2018|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|access-date=7 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190704232419/https://ew.com/awards/2018/12/10/the-favourite-critics-choice-award-nominations/|archive-date=4 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Theatre===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Role\n! scope=\"col\" | Director\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Venue\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| 2005\u20132006\n! scope=\"row\" | ''I Confess''\n| Mahmood\n| [[Andy Arnold]]\n| [[The Arches (Glasgow)|The Arches Theatre Company]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"scotsman1\"/>\n|-\n| 2005\u20132006\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[The Winter's Tale]]''\n| Florizel<br/>Cleomenes\n| Gordon Barr\n| Glasgow Repertory Company\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"scotsman1\"/>\n|-\n| 2006\u20132007\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Tom Fool''\n| Ludwig Meier\n| Clair Lizzimore\n| [[Citizens Theatre]]<br />[[Bush Theatre]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2006/nov/07/theatre2 |title=Tom Fool, Citizens, Glasgow |first=Mark |last=Fisher |website=[[The Guardian]] |date=7 November 2006 |access-date=3 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181113210643/https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2006/nov/07/theatre2 |archive-date=13 November 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2007/apr/04/theatre |title=Theatre review:Tom Fool / Bush, London |first=Lyn |last=Gardner |author-link=Lyn Gardner |website=[[The Guardian]] |date=4 April 2007 |access-date=3 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181113210544/https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2007/apr/04/theatre |archive-date=13 November 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n| 20