ramas-are-romanticising-rape-and-brothels-but-saying-the-word-talaaq-is-the-real-problem/ |title=Pakistani dramas are romanticising rape and brothels but saying the word \"talaaq\" is the real problem?  |access-date=26 March 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015\u20132016 ||''Riffat Aapa Ki Bahuein''|| Riffat Aapa || \n|-\n| 2016 ||''[[Udaari]]''|| Sheedan ||[[Hum Award for Most Impactful Character]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/magazine/instep-today/369738-udaari-receives-global-recognition-bbc-reports |title=Udaari receives global recognition, BBC reports |last=NewsBytes |website=The News International  |access-date=26 March 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2016 ||''[[Jhoot]]''|| Saleha || \n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Pakeezah (TV series)|Pakeeza]]''\n|\n|Writer<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/magazine/instep-today/100104-A-drama-on-the-struggles-of-the-modern-day-woman |title=A drama on the struggles of the modern day woman |last=Shabbir |first=Buraq |website=The News International  |access-date=26 March 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2016 || ''[[Commander Safeguard|Commander Safeguard's Mission: Clean Sweep: Jungle Main Mungle]]'' || Dirtee || Voice\n|-\n| 2016 || ''[[Seeta Bagri]] ''|| Nandani Das ||<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.pakistantoday.com.pk/2016/05/19/sarwat-gillani-bushra-ansari-land-roles-in-drama-about-hindu-minorities/sarwat-gillani-bushra-ansari-land-roles-in-drama-about-hindu-minorities/#main |title=Sarwat Gillani, Bushra Ansari land roles in drama about Hindu minorities  |access-date=26 March 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2017 || ''Shaadi Mubarak Ho'' || Shahnaz || \n|-\n| 2018 || ''[[Bay Dardi]]'' || Shafay's Mother ||<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/magazine/instep-today/314993-baydardi-explores-the-issue-of-hiv |title=Baydardi explores the issue of HIV |last=NewsBytes |website=The News International  |access-date=26 March 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2018 || ''[[Naulakha (TV series)|Naulakha]]''||Noor Jehan\n|<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://nation.com.pk/18-Jul-2018/naulakha-highlights-greed-and-lust-for-heritage |title=Naulakha highlights greed and lust for heritage |date=17 July 2018 |website=The Nation  |access-date=26 March 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[Deewar-e-Shab]]''\n|Sitara Jahan\n|<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://images.dawn.com/news/1181661 |title=Bushra Ansari, Asma Abbasi and Zara Noor Abbas are starring together in Hum TV's next period play |last=Haq |first=Irfan Ul |date=15 January 2019 |website=Images  |access-date=26 March 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|2020\n|''[[Zebaish]]'' \n|\n|Writer and actress\n|-\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Pakistani actresses]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commonscat}}\n* {{official website|http://bushraansari.com/}} \n* {{IMDb name|name=Bushra Ansari|id=2558798}}\n\n{{Pride of Performance for Arts}}\n{{Hum Awards hosts}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ansari, Bushra}}\n[[Category:Pakistani female singers]]\n[[Category:Pakistani stage actresses]]\n[[Category:Pakistani television actresses]]\n[[Category:Pakistani television producers]]\n[[Category:Pakistani dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:Pakistani comedians]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Pride of Performance]]\n[[Category:Lahore College for Women University alumni]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Pakistani voice actresses]]\n[[Category:20th-century Pakistani actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century Pakistani actresses]]\n[[Category:1956 births]]\n[[Category:Women television producers]]\n[[Category:Muhajir people]]\n[[Category:20th-century Pakistani women singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Pakistani women singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Bushra Ansari<br/>\u0628\u0634\u0631\u06cc\u0670 \u0627\u0646\u0635\u0627\u0631\u06cc\n| image              = \n| caption            = Ansari at HUM showcase\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| birth_name         = Bushra Bashir\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1956|5|15}}<ref name=karachi15may56>{{cite web|url=http://bushraansari.com|title=Bushra Ansari official website|accessdate=13 July 2019|quote=1953: Bushra Bashir was born on 15th May at the Lady Dufferin hospital in Karachi to parents Mehmooda Begum and Ahmad Bashir, a famous journalist & filmmaker.}}</ref>\n| birth_place        = [[Karachi]], [[Sindh]], [[Pakistan]]<ref name=karachi15may56/>\n| nationality        = Pakistani\n| alma_mater         = \n| occupation         = Actress, singer, producer, writer, model\n| years_active       = 1965\u2013present\n| spouse             = [[Iqbal Hussain]]\n| relatives          = [[Ahmad Bashir]] (father)<br/>[[Asma Abbas]] (sister)<br/>Sumbul Shahid (sister)\n| honours            = [[Pride of Performance]] (1989)\n| website            = \n}}\n\n'''Bushra Ansari''' is a [[Pakistani]] actress, comedian, singer and playwright who started her career as a child performer in the 1950s.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.pak101.com/c/celebrities/bio/110/Actresses_TV/Bushra_Ansari |title=Bushra Ansari biography, complete biography of Actresses (TV) Bushra Ansari |website=pak101.com |access-date=13 December 2017}}</ref> Ansari won numerous awards during her career, including the Presidential [[Pride of Performance]] Award in 1989 for her contributions to the arts of [[Pakistan]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Bushra Ansari |url=http://global.ptv.com.pk/BushraAnsariHost.asp |website=global.ptv.com.pk |publisher=Pakistan Television Corp |accessdate=7 July 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150511081609/http://global.ptv.com.pk/BushraAnsariHost.asp |archivedate=11 May 2015 }}</ref><ref name=tvwork>{{Cite web |url=http://tns.thenews.com.pk/gravitas-bushra-ansari/ |title=The gravitas of Bushra Ansari |last=Instep |date=5 August 2018 |website=TNS \u2013 The News on Sunday  |access-date=25 March 2019}}</ref><ref name=tvwork1>{{Cite web |url=https://en.dailypakistan.com.pk/lifestyle/bushra-ansari-announces-comeback-with-laughter-laden-aayegi-baraat-series/ |title=Bushra Ansari announces comeback with laughter-laden \u2018Aayegi Baraat\u2019 series |website=Daily Pakistan Global  |access-date=25 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nAnsari's first dramatic acting role was in one of Iqbal Ansari's productions.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://images.dawn.com/news/1177734 |title=Celebrities like Bushra Ansari bear the worst of ageism in Pakistan |last=Kari |first=Maria |date=5 June 2017 |work=Images |access-date=13 December 2017 }}</ref> She also appeared on PTV's most-watched shows, including ''[[Angan Terha]]'', ''Show Time'', ''Show Sha'', ''Rang Tarang'', ''Emergency Ward'' and the sketch comedy TV series ''[[Fifty Fifty (comedy show)|Fifty Fifty]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm2558798/ |title=Bushra Ansari |publisher=IMDb |access-date=13 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://pakistani.pk/bushra-ansari/ |title=Bushra Ansari Drama List, Family, Height, Age, Family, Net Worth |last=Shah |first=Saud |website=Pakistani.PK \u2013 Your Local Guide to Business Listings, Restaurants, Hotels &amp; Product Reviews  |access-date=13 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://nation.com.pk/19-Nov-2017/a-session-with-bushra-ansari |title=A session with Bushra Ansari |work=The Nation |access-date=13 December 2017 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://nation.com.pk/22-Nov-2017/bushra-ansari-marks-universal-children-s-day |title=Bushra Ansari marks Universal Children's Day |work=The Nation |access-date=13 December 2017 }}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n=== Film ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Film !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n|2013\n|''[[Abhi To Main Jawan Hoon#Remake|Abhi To Main Jawan Hoon]]''\n|\n|Telefilm\n|-\n|2015||''[[Jawani Phir Nahi Ani]]''||Zoya's Mother ||\n|-\n|2016||''[[Ho Mann Jahaan]]''|| Nadir's Mother||\n|}\n\n=== Telefilm ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !!Telefilm!! Role !! Notes\n|-\n|2013|| ''Ghoonghat'' || ||\n|-\n|2014|| ''Hoo Bahoo''|| ||\n|-\n|2015|| 